blog.description:
All the photographs posted here are original work from photographers I follow  on tumblr . My aim is  twofold, share the inspiration, and give photographers a bit more exposure .     
 I am also part of the  Lux Lit  team of rebloggers, and ms-excuse me with Thierry Facon, where the main focus is to bring you lesser known photographs that we feel deserve some more attention. 
 Please feel free to contact me if you have any questions or comments, or would  like me to check out your blog;  I'm on a constant quest for new photography blogs to follow .
julesfalkhunter@gmail.com

summary: [Image Description: A painterly styled piece of fanart of Marion Lavorre, also known as the Ruby of the Sea, from Critical Role....
body:
[Image Description: A painterly styled piece of fanart of Marion Lavorre, also known as the Ruby of the Sea, from Critical Role. She’s a red skinned tiefling, wearing a gold patterned strapless dress, has long, curly red hair, golden eyes, and curled horns. She’s going down a staircase, and is singing. End Description]

I love Marion Lavorre a lot, and her interactions with Jester. They have such a good mother/daughter relationship.

This took a total of 8+ hours, since it was soft shaded, but I’m super happy with how it came out!
